    {
        "content": "<p>I have recently been reading a lot about relative categories and simplicial localization, and while simplicial localization gives all simplicial categories up to DK equivalence (there's a Quillen equivalence to the Bergner model structure), <em>I am particularly interested in the case when we localize a <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/relative%20category\">[[relative category]]</a> that is actually a model category.</em> This is a broad reference-request question, specific tools or general theorems are equally appreciated. </p>\n<p>Couple findings:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>The case of presentable simplicial model categories is solved at the appendix of HTT (these are locally presentable quasicategories).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Simplicial localization sends <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub><mo>↪</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C_{cf}\\hookrightarrow C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9694em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">c</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↪</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> to a DK equivalence, i.e. <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>L</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub><mo>≅</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">LC_{cf}\\cong LC</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9694em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">c</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 261559646,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1637010681
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I also feel that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>L</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">LC_{cf}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9694em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">c</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is already a Kan-enriched category, but couldn't write this down precisely (yet)</p>",
        "id": 261559767,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1637010726
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What gives you the impression that simplicial localisation gives you a Kan-enriched category? My impression is that this basically never happens.</p>",
        "id": 261567073,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhen Lin Low",
        "timestamp": 1637014212
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The relative category of combinatorial model categories is Dwyer–Kan equivalent to the relative category of presentable quasicategories: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2110.04679\">https://arxiv.org/abs/2110.04679</a></p>",
        "id": 261599486,
        "sender_full_name": "Dmitri Pavlov",
        "timestamp": 1637040345
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"416301\">Zhen Lin Low</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/simplicial.20localization.20of.20model.20categories/near/261567073\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What gives you the impression that simplicial localisation gives you a Kan-enriched category? My impression is that this basically never happens.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That was because at the original DK paper a \"homotopy\" between zig-zags is a hammock e.g.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/51Cjtw2dbNhZj6WZc1-tQMQD/image.png\">image.png</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/51Cjtw2dbNhZj6WZc1-tQMQD/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/51Cjtw2dbNhZj6WZc1-tQMQD/image.png\"></a></div><p>In general there is nothing more to say, but from Whitehead's theorem in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C_{cf}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9694em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">c</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> the vertical weak equivalences are actually homotopy equivalences, implying there is at least a \"partial hammock\"</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/sBtMI0Bstmyj_N55f3QZWoiA/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/sBtMI0Bstmyj_N55f3QZWoiA/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/sBtMI0Bstmyj_N55f3QZWoiA/image.png\"></a></div><p>where the vertical arrows are homotopy equivalent to the identity. However, I think that the bottom square isn't commutative with the dashed arrow. At most there is a huge diagram</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/XG9DZHJ8MRVxkTBXKDCa-NPD/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/XG9DZHJ8MRVxkTBXKDCa-NPD/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/XG9DZHJ8MRVxkTBXKDCa-NPD/image.png\"></a></div><p>(where again the square with a dashed arrow doesn't seem to commute)</p>",
        "id": 261646417,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Teixeira",
        "timestamp": 1637072166
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this idea probably stemmed from the desire of having a oo-category with the objects and morphisms of the model category, and as 2-morphisms homotopy equivalences; it's likely another case of slogan-pushing, so maybe it shouldn't be taken much seriously</p>",
        "id": 261646728,
